{"key":"processedPost-10153987","value":{"id":10153987,"first":10149974,"last":10155656,"when":1239585806,"utime":"04/13/09 04:23 AM","content":"Like rotten apples, all it takes is one to spoil the whole batch.&nbsp; Next time, don't waste your spores on a silly LC.&nbsp; New growers push those, but you won't find many experienced growers ever recommending it.&nbsp; Sugar water favors bacteria, and you never know if it's good or not unless you have a microscope until your jars fail, and then you've lost a month or more.<br />If you want to move up, make petri dishes and test your spores on agar, and then when you have a clean culture, use it to inoculate your grains.&nbsp; That way, you KNOW you have a good culture going.&nbsp; However, you should still sniff each and every jar before use.&nbsp; I do.<br />RR","title":"Re: repetitive stalling......"}}